syd:comment.syd:text: This comment has been written in the description field of the SubSystem "0_Setpoint_Correction".

w:r.w:t: checks if the description parameter of a SubSystem isn’t empty to add its content as a paragraph to the corresponding section in the document.
It also detects all the docblocks included in the SubSystem to add a paragraph per block.
Thus, the comments you read in this section are coming from the description of the current system and the DocBlock called “Another paragraph”.
generate several documents with different layouts, styles and even contents from a single model
. Therefore, the concept of “profile” has been defined.
For the end-user, each menu items in the “Generate Document” group of the “File” menu is a profile.
In detail, each profile defines in particular:
Where the document file will be automatically saved and with which name,
The security level of the generated document (to hide secured content from the model),
The layout and style of the document (with the help of a style-sheet),
The above parameters repeated several times to generate several documents with a single profile.
